F-0043 ACCEPTANCE #1/#2 DEMONSTRATION

Goal: with a REAL feature marked in_progress in the LIVE roadmap/features.json,
scripts/test-hooks.sh reports 0 failures. The 6 previously-failing permissive tests now
read an isolated zero-in_progress STATE_FILE fixture (hook_file_z / STATE_FILE="$ZSTATE"),
immune to live in_progress state. This was the bug that forced F-0040/F-0041 to stay
'pending' during their builds, and that made 'bash scripts/verify.sh' FAIL for the whole
duration of every build.

PROCEDURE (throwaway local step; live backlog reverted, never committed in_progress):
  1. mark F-0043 in_progress via the sanctioned writer (scripts/update-state.ts) — the
     exact /work loop step-1 state that previously broke the gate.
  2. run scripts/test-hooks.sh; capture output to a TEMP file OUTSIDE roadmap/evidence so
     the F-DM1 hermeticity contract test does not observe this log being written mid-run.
  3. revert F-0043 to pending on EXIT.

RESULT:
  live in_progress during run : F-0043
  test-hooks.sh exit code     : 0    (0 = all hook contract tests pass)
  summary                     : hook contract tests: 367 passed, 0 failed
  [FAIL] count                : 0

ACCEPTANCE #1 met: 0 failures with a real feature in_progress (the 6 permissive tests are
now fixture-isolated). ACCEPTANCE #2 met: see verify.log (VERIFY: PASS, exit 0) — the gate
passes; combined with this run, the gate would pass during a build with a feature in_progress.

The 6 isolated permissive cases + the F-0043 meta-test, all PASS under live in_progress:
  [PASS] allows other files
  [PASS] allows other features.json outside roadmap
  [PASS] allows file mentioning it in content only
  [PASS] sed branch still allows other files
